Progress

Purpose:
- Public-safe active operational progress memory for MemoryEndpoints.com implementation, verification, deployment, and dogfooding work.

Verification status: active operational memory; verify with the `.uai` audit before relying on it.
Memory scope: current progress, verification evidence pointers, and completion boundary.
Public-safe status: safe for source control; contains no credential values.
Update route: replace stale facts with public-safe current state here; submit durable summaries to https://memoryendpoints.com/api/matm/memory-events/submit when authenticated.
Source of truth: current repository state, command output, verification reports, Git commits, and `.uai/totem.uai`.
Next action for agents: keep this file date-free, concise, and current; do not use it as a dated changelog.
Must not expose: raw API keys, bearer tokens, FTP credentials, database passwords, private keys, private handoff payloads, raw one-time keys, or unredacted deployment handoff values.

Current progress state:
- MemoryEndpoints.com has a pure stdlib WSGI MATM app with public discovery routes, protected workspace memory, current-message coordination, notification acknowledgement, redacted receipts, memory firewall, review queue, idempotency, file storage, and optional stdlib SQLite relational storage.
- Operator Console v1 local work converts the human console from always-visible raw JSON panes into workspace summary cards, filterable memory rows, review queue rows with promotion controls, inbox rows, receipt rows, audit rows, and collapsible debug JSON. Verification covers desktop and mobile-width console layout, memory save/search/filtering, review promotion through integration tests, broadcast row rendering, acknowledgement, receipt display, and live HTTP/API smoke checks.
- Live console polish includes message delivery feedback rows, compact workflow anchors for workspace, memory, reviews, messages, and receipts/audit, and copy-safe row actions for memory, message, notification, receipt, and audit ids.
- Live console coordination polish adds an all-lane inbox overview for the human verifier, Codex, and swarm observer lanes so operators can see unread counts, open each lane without manually refreshing one agent at a time, and keep the lane overview current after acknowledgements.
- Local message delivery polish adds API-backed broadcast/targeted delivery metadata, inbox agent filters, delivery counts, and matching operator row rendering so humans do not need to infer message routing from nested JSON; deploy only after this source is committed and live SHA verification can match.
- Live home page polish makes the first screen more operational and less hero-heavy by replacing the decorative memory-flow block with compact entry links for console, readiness, memory lifecycle, and transparency.
- Public memory search responses normalize firewall metadata for human-safe display: `valuesRedacted` is true on returned events and firewall blocks, while `redactionApplied` reports whether sensitive content was actually redacted.
- Dogfood coordination hygiene has the human verifier current-message lane cleared of stale handled unread messages through acknowledgement receipts; receipt and audit readback remain redacted with no raw credential or payload exposure.
- Protected search is now aligned with dogfooding hosted MemoryEndpoints workspace memory and supports operator filters for scope, memory type, review status, promotion state, tag, and actor. Source-controlled `docs/long-term-memory` files remain migration seeds and evidence artifacts rather than the protected workspace search source.
- Live memory submission polish adds an API-backed submission summary with memory id, review id, firewall decision, review state, redaction state, and payload-hidden status, plus a visible console confirmation row after saving memory.
- Live console search polish exposes the full protected memory filter set in the human UI, including promotion state and actor agent filters, renders active filter chips above result rows, groups hosted memory rows by account/company/workspace/project scope, and adds a clear-filters action so operators can recover from narrow dogfood searches without opening debug JSON.
- Live console audit polish adds action and limit filters to the audit panel, renders active audit filter chips only for intentional filters, and keeps the clear action from leaving stale default-limit chips behind.
- Live audit detail polish adds redacted audit detail summaries for route, counts, filters, source, and delivery counts, and renders those summaries in audit rows so operators do not need to open debug JSON for common audit context.
- Live review queue polish adds API-backed active status filters, queue-wide status counts, and detected-threat row metadata so operators can understand pending, quarantined, promoted, and rejected review lanes without opening review JSON.
- Live lane overview polish renders API-backed broadcast and targeted delivery counts in the all-agent inbox overview so operators can compare human, Codex, and observer lanes without opening each inbox.
- Live debug-view polish hides raw console JSON panels by default behind a single advanced debug toggle, keeping API-shaped payloads available for engineering verification while making the default human console read as operator rows and cards.
- Live workspace operator-summary polish adds a compact `operatorSummary` contract to protected workspace reads, drives the console boundary/storage/privacy cards from that summary, and records redacted hierarchy readiness in audit details so humans do not need the full workspace JSON for normal verification.
- Live two-way UI coordination smoke proves Codex-to-observer targeted delivery, observer-to-Codex response delivery, target inbox visibility, stale inbox overwrite prevention, redacted inbox rows, hidden debug JSON by default, no desktop/mobile overflow, and MultiAgentMemory.com links.
- Local operator-summary expansion adds compact API-backed summaries for protected memory search, current-message inboxes, and receipts, and renders summary badges for hosted counts, scopes, review states, response dispositions, consumers, and payload-hidden status; deploy only after this source is committed and live SHA verification can match.
- Local memory search operator-summary polish adds API-backed hosted-memory counts for scope, memory type, review status, and promotion state, renders those counts above console memory rows, and records redacted scope/review count summaries in audit details so verification searches can be assessed without tallying JSON; deploy only after this source is committed and live SHA verification can match.
- Local inbox operator-summary polish adds API-backed current-message/inbox counts for unread messages, broadcast versus targeted delivery, and required-response versus acknowledgement-only lanes, renders those counts above inbox rows, and records redacted response count summaries in audit details; deploy only after this source is committed and live SHA verification can match.
- Local receipt operator-summary polish adds API-backed receipt counts by status and consumer agent, payload-hidden status, receipt summary chips in the console, and redacted receipt count summaries in audit details so receipt verification does not require raw JSON; deploy only after this source is committed and live SHA verification can match.
- Live console boundary polish adds a compact account -> company -> workspace -> project chain above workspace summary cards and copy-safe account, company, workspace, and project id actions.
- Live console session polish adds a compact post-load status strip for live/local surface, account/company/workspace/project hierarchy readiness, key privacy, active agent lane, and shortcut actions so human verifiers get operator status before entering the lower workflows.
- Live console review-decision polish adds a visible operator confirmation row after promote, reject, or quarantine decisions so humans do not need to open decision JSON to confirm status, reviewer, memory id, redaction, and payload-hidden state.
- Live console acknowledgement polish adds a visible receipt confirmation row after marking one or more inbox notifications read, including consumer, receipt id, notification id, redaction, and payload-hidden state; live browser smoke verifies the row against a temporary UI smoke lane with payloads hidden.
- Live console receipt filter polish adds an explicit consumer-agent filter and clear action for receipts, API-backed active filter metadata, and receipt filter chips so operators can inspect human, Codex, observer, or current inbox receipts without relying on hidden inbox state.
- Live console message polish adds redacted delivery metadata and broadcast/targeted counts to message submit and inbox readbacks so operators can confirm delivery type, response disposition, and lane counts without opening raw payloads.
- The `docs/long-term-memory` migration helper submits reviewed markdown memory records into hosted MemoryEndpoints workspace memory with stable idempotency keys. Live migration evidence shows eight source-controlled long-term memory records submitted, searched from hosted memory, and promoted through the review queue with redacted report output at `docs/reports/long-term-memory-migration.json` and `docs/reports/long-term-memory-promotion.json`.
- Human-verifier dogfood memory now includes a company/account boundary verification row that is visible through the normal `verification` console search alongside workspace and project verification rows. Redacted evidence is stored at `docs/reports/human-verifier-boundary-memory-repair.json`.
- MultiAgentMemory.com is plain static HTML/CSS companion documentation under `sites/multiagentmemory.com/`; it links to MemoryEndpoints.com and the GitHub repository and explains how the system works.
- Local verification passes through unit and integration tests, WSGI public-route verification, static companion-site verification, `.uai` audit, package verification, secret scan, enterprise readiness audit checks, and whitespace diff check.
- Repository boundary audit is rerunnable and passes with `E:\MemoryEndpoints.com` as the only active MemoryEndpoints/MultiAgentMemory source tree, `sites/multiagentmemory.com/` as the companion docs source, no duplicate product folders at the drive root, and no root-level runtime artifacts.
- Local `.uai` memory is required to remain active always. It is hot startup memory, not a dated changelog, and this file must stay date-free.
- MemoryEndpoints.com is the MATM update destination at `https://memoryendpoints.com/api/matm/memory-events/submit`; UAIX wizard URLs are setup guidance only.
- The UAIX setup option is `https://uaix.org/en-us/tools/ai-memory-package-wizard/#setup-MATM-MemoryEndpoints`.
- MemoryEndpoints.com inbound links should use `https://memoryendpoints.com`; it currently has one setup surface.
- Strategy intake has been distilled into reviewed long-term docs for enterprise engineering, MATM architecture, timestamp-free memory, and system targets.
- Raw strategy reports and prompt drafts remain local-only and must not be committed.
- `/api/version` exposes public-safe build provenance and the verifier can require the live `build.sourceSha` to match the current Git head before claiming latest-code deployment.
- Live MemoryEndpoints.com public routes, latest-code SHA verification, latest protected audit-log dogfood contract, MySQL backend verification, console asset smoke, and enterprise readiness checks are verified for the deployed surface.
- Live MultiAgentMemory.com companion documentation is published through the FileZilla-backed explicit FTPS path and live static-site verification passes for expected docs and discovery files.
- MemoryEndpoints.com explicit FTPS connection check passes through the FileZilla-backed profile and live upload succeeds to the login root; plain FTP remains rejected and should not be used while FTPS works.
- GitHub Actions CI is not required as a completion gate per human direction; the public checker previously saw the pushed commit's job fail before workflow steps due to an account billing-lock annotation, so do not keep retrying it unless re-enabled.
- Dogfood status: Live MATM dogfood run verified against `https://memoryendpoints.com`; report `docs/reports/dogfood-memory-run.json`; local audit-log readback verified: true; live audit-log readback verified: true; MATM update URL `https://memoryendpoints.com/api/matm/memory-events/submit`; raw credential values stored in report: false.
- Completion must not be claimed until current-commit local verification, deploy, live SHA verification, live route verification, dogfood, package, secret scan, and gated capability documentation are current.
